timeline.bodyText:
I think we should return a java.security.cert.X509Certificate just like getCertificateChain().
BTW, I just noticed this in lines 96-98:
if (!(c instanceof PK11Cert)) {
    logger.error("JSSKeyManager: Can't cast to PK11Cert: " + c);
}

This code is only logging an error message, but the actual error will happen later in line 101:
list.add((PK11Cert) c);

I think we can just remove lines 96-98 because line 101 will generate another error message.
Ideally org.mozilla.jss.crypto.X509Certificate should extend java.security.cert.X509Certificate, but that's a separate issue.

