replies.bodyText:
Yeah, I'm not suggesting to fix the X509Certificate hierarchy now :)
But if we do, I think the InternalCertificate and  TokenCertificate can be merged into org.mozilla.jss.crypto.X509Certificate (or PK11Cert) which will then extend java.security.cert.X509Certificate.
I'll let you decide on the return type of getCertificate(). Even if we pick org.mozilla.jss.crypto.X509Certificate, when we eventually fix the hierarchy it shouldn't be much of an issue anymore.
About the type casting, I think something like this will make more sense:
logger.debug("JSSKeyManager: - " + c.getSubjectDN());
if (c instanceof PK11Cert) {
    list.add((PK11Cert) c);
} else {
    throw new ClassCastException("Can't cast " + c.getClass().getName() + " to PK11Cert: " + c.getSubjectDN());
}

No big deal, I'll leave that up to you. The code looks fine regardless. ACK.
